22 §3173. Powers of the Board of Regents; coordination with management boards
23 A. In coordination with each management board of a public
24 postsecondary institution, the Board of Regents shall have the power to set
25 policy regarding each of the following:
26 (1) Accreditation of public postsecondary institutions.
27 (2) Specialized accreditation of any individual program or unit at a
28 public postsecondary institution where such accreditation is required.
29 B. The Board of Regents shall adopt policies to allow a public
30 postsecondary institution, subject to the approval of the institution's
