11 (1) Identify a list of units, programs, and professional schools that
12 require specialized accreditation and a corresponding list of recognized
13 accreditors.
14 (2) Adopt policies, in coordination with the management boards, to
15 ensure that each program or unit requiring specialized accreditation remains
16 accredited at all times by an accreditor from the list of accreditors maintained
17 by the Board of Regents.
18 §3174. Process for accreditation; applications; accreditors
19 A. A public postsecondary institution may seek a new accreditor for the
20 institution or for a specialized program or unit so long as the selection of an
21 accreditor and the process of seeking accreditation complies with this Chapter.
22 B. If a public postsecondary institution seeks a new accreditor, the
23 institution shall apply for approval with the institution's management board.
24 C. The public postsecondary institution shall seek an accreditor that
25 prioritizes all of the following:
26 (1) Promotes credential success and workforce outcomes.
27 (2) Promotes educational quality and affordability.
28 (3) Promotes financial stability of the public postsecondary institutions.
29 (4) Ensures appropriate accountability through a rigorous annual review
30 of the faculty.
