5 §3175. Management boards of public postsecondary institutions
6 A. If a public postsecondary institution applies for a new accreditor, as
7 provided in R.S. 17:3174, the management board shall do all of the following:
8 (1) Review the institution's application and determine if the proposed
9 accreditor meets the standards and requirements set forth in this Chapter.
10 (2) Determine if the application for a new accreditor complies with the
11 policies set forth by the Board of Regents, as provided in R.S. 17:3173.
12 B. With respect to a public postsecondary institution's accreditor or any
13 application for a new accreditor, the management board shall, in coordination
14 with the Board of Regents, do all of the following:
15 (1) Ensure that each public postsecondary institution that is under the
16 management board's jurisdiction shall post on the institution's website the
17 status of its accreditation and other documentation that the management board
18 deems relevant that has been submitted to the accreditor to gain or maintain
19 accreditation.
20 (2) Specify the manner and frequency that the institution is to notify or
21 update the public on the progress of reaccreditation with the same accreditor
22 or the process of accreditation with a new accreditor through the institution's
23 website.
24 §3176. Prohibited accreditors
25 Notwithstanding any other provision of law to the contrary, no
26 accreditor may be chosen that conditions accreditation upon any violation of the
27 Constitution of Louisiana or any state law.
